import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Release_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Release_Date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('US_Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide_Gross')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Release_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Release_Date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot([data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'], data['IMDB_Rating']])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Rotten Tomatoes Rating: {:.2f}'.format(data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'].median()), 'IMDB Rating: {:.2f}'.format(data['IMDB_Rating'].median())])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
